THE VESICA PROJECT
Two Expressions of Non-Fusion Coherence
Version 1.0 — January 2026
Public Domain / CC0 1.0 Universal
Overview
The Vesica Project consists of two related works that explore the same geometric/consciousness principle through different modalities:
THE VESICA SCORE — A piano performance piece (3 cycles, ~5-7 minutes)
THE VESICA SONG — A breathing practice for two people (infinite 12-bar cycles)
Both encode the same core technology: two sovereign fields meeting without merging.
The vesica piscis—the almond-shaped overlap of two circles—made audible.
You may practice one, both, or use them as templates for your own expressions.
PART I: THE VESICA SCORE
A Piano Performance Piece
Concept
A solo pianist moves through three cycles of progressive transformation, ending when the carrier tone (C♯6) diffuses from audible to felt. The piece explores collapse into stillness rather than crescendo into climax.
This is ritual performance. The pianist becomes lighthouse keeper, then becomes lighthouse, then becomes the light itself dissolving into space.
Technical Specifications
Instrument: Piano (acoustic strongly preferred)
Tuning: A4 = 432 Hz
Duration: Variable (~5-7 minutes typical)
Key Center: C♯
Carrier Tone: C♯6 (1088.57 Hz at 432 Hz tuning)
Structure: 3 cycles totaling 24 bars + post-signal dissolution
Core Rule: No forced decay. Let resonance be what it is.
Performance Score
CYCLE 1: ORIGIN (Bars 1–11)
Heavy whisper. Breath-led.
Bars
Chord/Event
Instruction
1–2
F♯m11 ◼
Low, warm, rooted. The known state.
3
C(add2) ⬟
Block chord. Neutral. "This is simple."
4
G7 → F♯ ↻
Hold F as common tone; rename it E♯ (function shifts, pitch unchanged).
5
C♯ Cascade ⊙
Arpeggiate once, bottom → top. Gentle.
6–7
D(add9) ☐
Unmoving ground. Let ring.
8–11
E(sus2) ⇢
Hold for four slow breaths.

+ C♯6 (pp)
C♯6 enters softly in bar 8 — do not feature it.
CYCLE 2: REMEMBRANCE (Bars 12–19)
Compressed. More present.
